> Is there specific required input and output format for this *.ort model file? My model takes [batch size, img channel, img h, img w] I wonder if there is some required format for it.

The ORT format model should have the same inputs and outputs as the original ONNX model. You can call [Run()](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/api/c/struct_ort_api.html#ad8b12cad4160d43da92f49191cd91895) on the session the same way for either type of model.
How do we know what the inputs to a model are supposed to be?

> How do we know what the inputs to a model are supposed to be?

One easy way to find out is to examine the model in [Netron](https://netron.app/).

Thanks for the suggestion! It helped me get closer to solving my issue. Once is used Netron to get the inputs and image name fixed, I ran into another issue because I'm swapping from using the ORT file in the example to an ORT that my team
 created. 
Since you already helped with this issue. I went ahead and created a different github issue here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11541
Thanks again!

The link from https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-inference-examples/tree/main/mobile/examples/object_detection/ios/README.md has been fixed.
Closing this issue for now. If you have particular questions about the info at https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/ort-format-models.html#convert-onnx-models-to-ort-format feel free to re-open or create a new issue.
